description.narrative: The fourth Development Policy Support Program (DPSP-4) is the fourth such operation in Indonesia. It is in substantive terms a continuation of DPSPs 1-3, the programmatic series of annual single-tranche operations from 2005 to 2007. The DPSP series-cofinancing the Development Policy Loan (DPL) series supported by the World Bank and the Government of Japan-is embedded in the Government's Medium-Term National Development Plan (RPJM) for 2004-2009. It supports the RPJM's broad goals of stimulating higher and sustainable economic growth with lower levels of unemployment and poverty, in three core areas: (i) investment climate, (ii) enhanced public financial management and governance, and (iii) public service delivery to the poor. The DPSP-4 is also proposed as a single-tranche operation based on completed actions demonstrating satisfactory progress. It builds on reforms undertaken during past DPSPs and sets the groundwork for an expanded policy dialogue for future operations.
